diagnoses: justification: Mastocytosis can cause all of the listed symptoms. Easy bleeding and angioedema are due to mast cell release of mediators like histamine and heparin. Seizure disorders can occur due to central nervous system involvement. Wheezing can be triggered by mast cell mediators causing bronchospasm. Difficulty concentrating can be a result of histamine release or other inflammatory mediators affecting the brain.}, {diagnosis: Anaphylaxis

justification: Anaphylaxis can cause all the listed symptoms, although it is an acute, rather than chronic, condition.  Easy bleeding is less common but can occur with disseminated intravascular coagulation (DIC) as a complication. Seizures and wheezing are due to airway constriction and low blood pressure. Angioedema is a hallmark symptom. Difficulty concentrating can occur during or after an episode due to low oxygen levels.}, {diagnosis: Hereditary angioedema (HAE)

justification: HAE is characterized by recurrent episodes of angioedema, which can cause airway obstruction (wheezing). While not directly causing seizures, airway compromise can lead to hypoxia and seizures.  Easy bleeding is less common but can occur in some HAE subtypes. Difficulty concentrating may occur due to anxiety or as a consequence of repeated episodes.}, {diagnosis: Systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE)

justification: SLE is an autoimmune disease that can affect multiple organ systems.  It can cause easy bleeding due to low platelet counts or clotting factor deficiencies. Seizures can result from central nervous system inflammation.  Wheezing can occur with lung involvement (lupus pneumonitis). Angioedema is less common but can occur. Difficulty concentrating (brain fog) is a common symptom of SLE.}, {diagnosis: Drug reaction with eosinophilia and systemic symptoms (DRESS syndrome)

justification: DRESS syndrome is a severe drug reaction characterized by fever, rash, lymphadenopathy, and multi-organ involvement.  It can cause all the listed symptoms. Easy bleeding can occur with liver involvement or low platelet counts.  Seizures can result from brain inflammation.  Wheezing can be a sign of lung involvement. Angioedema is common. Difficulty concentrating can occur due to inflammation and other systemic effects.}, {diagnosis: Antiphospholipid syndrome (APS)

justification: APS is an autoimmune disorder characterized by blood clots and pregnancy complications.  Easy bleeding is unusual but can occur with catastrophic APS (a rare but severe form).  Seizures can occur due to blood clots in the brain. Wheezing is less common but can occur with pulmonary embolism (blood clot in the lung). Angioedema is not typical. Difficulty concentrating (brain fog) is common in APS.}, {diagnosis: Tumor lysis syndrome (TLS)

justification: TLS is an oncological emergency that occurs when tumor cells release their contents into the bloodstream, disrupting electrolyte balance.  This can cause easy bleeding due to clotting abnormalities. Seizures can occur due to electrolyte disturbances. Wheezing is less common but can occur with fluid buildup in the lungs. Angioedema is not typical. Difficulty concentrating can occur due to metabolic derangements.}, {diagnosis: Thrombotic thrombocytopenic purpura (TTP)

justification: TTP is a rare blood disorder characterized by low platelets, hemolytic anemia, and blood clots.  It can cause easy bleeding (a hallmark symptom) and seizures (due to blood clots in the brain).  Wheezing is less common but can occur with pulmonary complications.  Angioedema is not typical.  Difficulty concentrating can occur due to low oxygen levels or other complications.}, {diagnosis: Meningitis/encephalitis

justification: Infection of the brain and/or spinal cord (meningitis/encephalitis) can cause seizures and altered mental status (including difficulty concentrating).  While less common, some infections can cause bleeding disorders or trigger angioedema. Wheezing may occur if there is respiratory involvement or aspiration.}, {diagnosis: Vasculitis

justification: Vasculitis refers to inflammation of blood vessels.  Depending on the type and location, it can cause a wide range of symptoms, including easy bleeding (if blood vessels are damaged), seizures (if brain vessels are involved), wheezing (if lung vessels are affected), angioedema (due to inflammation), and difficulty concentrating (due to inflammation or other organ involvement).}
